Program: Last Word
Title: Eric Tomlinson, Elsie Tu, Peter Dickinson, Lillian Vernon and Lemmy
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b06spffh
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 3 Jan 2016
Recording engineer, Eric Tomlinson, who worked on the score for Star Wars and added music to Charlie Chaplin's silent films. Elsie Tu, social campaigner, legislator and educationalist in Hong Kong. Author, Peter Dickinson, who twice received the prestigious Carnegie medal for his work. Entrepreneur, Lillian Vernon, whose catalogue business was the first company owned by a woman to be listed on the US Stock Exchange. Motorhead frontman, Lemmy, who's credited with introducing punk sounds into heavy metal. Producer: Maire Devine Show less